Defendant William E. Erickson appeared by video, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant given complaint; charges/penalties explained by the court. Defendant is referred to State Public Defenders Office. Minutes filed.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant is not to enter any bars, taverns, or liquor stores. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant is to be booked and printed within twenty-four (24) hours. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH V.S. OR HER RESIDENCE. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
